The post-[[1372 DR]] version of this spell required only verbal and somatic components plus the priest's [[holy symbol]] or [[divine focus]]. After the [[Second Sundering]], the spell required all three standard components, where the [[material component]] was lit incense, and lasted up to ten minutes.

The ''speak with dead'' that [[Tessaril Winter]] learned required a drop of the caster's blood, a sprig of mint, a sprig of parsley, and red or black [[gem]] worth at least 100 gp that had been crushed to powder.
